    public interface Versions
extends Service, VersionsTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService

    • Method Detail

      • get

        Versions.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String name,
                           java.lang.String version)
        Returns information about a given component version in the depot.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the given component

        Operation Errors:
        Error - If there is unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        NotFound - if component with given version is not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleSettings.Read.

        Parameters:
        name - Name of the component The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.settings.component.
        version - Version of the component
        Returns:
        instance of Versions.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
